description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit an enthusiastic and creative Support Worker to work within the Early Intervention Service across the county of Dorset to support individuals with a serious mental illness to have access to physical health monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new post in the team. . The post will be attractive to support workers who feel strongly about advocating physical health for people with a serious mental illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working closely with the existing teams in Primary and Secondary care to enhance the existing provision by providing comprehensive physical health assessments, signpost individuals to services to improve their physical health and set goals with individuals to help improve their physical health in their local communities and supporting social inclusion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will provide excellent opportunities for effective partnership working with a range of organisations across primary and secondary services and will be supported by senior healthcare professionals from both primary and secondary services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunity for the right candidate to develop online physical health groups for service users supported by staff in the existing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who can put individual’s needs at the heart of the job, keep people safe, contribute to their care and respond compassionately to suffering as well as someone who can communicate well with people. This will be a permanent full time post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to a vehicle will be essential to enable the practitioner to engage service users across the county of Dorset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alicia Sharp Physical Health Lead or Simon Potterton Acting/Interim Service Manager Early Intervention Service on 01202 584336&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
